description:
A History of Art in Africa
Harry N. Abrams, Inc. | 2001 | ISBN: 0810934485 | English | 550 pages | PDF | 138 MB


Informed by the latest scholarship yet written for the general reader, this is the first comprehensive book to present the arts of Africa in art-historical terms. The authors treat individual pieces as tangible manifestations of changing beliefs and customs, as products of complex cultural interactions, as expressions of historical and economic realities, and as creations of gifted individuals, and in so doing brilliantly offer up African art on its own terms
